TI: [Effect of prolonged interaction of mice with aggressive and submissive types of behavior on the concentration of serotonin, 5-hydroxyindoleacetic acid and noradrenalin in the brain].
AB: As a result of repeated experience of victories and defeats in mice of C57BL/6 line, submissive and aggressive types of behaviour were elaborated, the stabilization of which was accompanied by a change in serotonin and noradrenaline content in various parts of the brain, at least of two kinds. Nonspecific unindirected changes in transmitter' levels found in both groups of animals in comparison with the control, are apparently due to the experience of zoosocial contracts. Changes were also noted connected with specificity of the observed behaviour.
TT: Effekt dlitel'nogo vzaimodeistviia myshei s agressivnym i podchinennym tipami povedeniia na soderzhanie serotonina, 5-gidroksiindoluksusnoi kisloty i noradrenalina v mozge.
TA: Zh Vyssh Nerv Deiat Im I P Pavlova
JT: Zhurnal vysshei nervnoi deiatelnosti imeni I P Pavlova
SO: Zh Vyssh Nerv Deiat Im I P Pavlova. 1985 Sep-Oct;35(5):879-83.
